message.content:
1. There are twenty-one male patients.
2. These patients have suppressed plasma HIV-RNA.
3. These patients are on cART.
4. These patients have a known HIV infection.
5. The duration of their known HIV infection is 9.2 years.
6. The interquartile range (IQR) of their known HIV infection duration is between 6.9 and 13.5 years.
7. These patients have been using abacavir.
8. The duration of their abacavir use is 6.5 years.
9. The interquartile range (IQR) of their abacavir use is between 2.8 and 9.3 years.

messages.content:
Statement: Twenty-one male patients with suppressed plasma HIV-RNA, on cART, had a known HIV infection for 9.2 years (IQR 6.9–13.5) with abacavir use for 6.5 years (2.8–9.3).

List all the facts we explicitly know from the statement. Make each fact as atomic as possible.
